<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="92.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,187,212]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Bierman)" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bierman" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[328,608,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavo">
<emphasis box="[328,485,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Rhotana pavo</emphasis>
(Bierman)
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Zelazny &amp; Webb, 2011" authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" box="[821,941,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[821,941,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">R. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[948,1035,188,211]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from New 
<collectingCountry box="[1164,1248,188,212]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. It can be distinguished by the forewings having stramineous apical crossveins, a thin lining of red along the veins separating the forewing marks, and by the last subcostal sector lacking a prominent red mark. In addition, the left lobe of the male aedeagus clearly surpasses the right lobe. Although the differences to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmidt)" baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" box="[970,1229,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Decora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biermani">
<emphasis box="[970,1105,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">R. biermani</emphasis>
(Schmidt)
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry name="Indonesia" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Maluku Islands</collectingCountry>
are not clear, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bierman" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[388,473,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavo">
<emphasis box="[388,473,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">R. pavo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is darker, has slightly separated facial carinae, and large subantennal processes.
</paragraph>
